VARIABLE ACROSSPLAZA
VARIABLE CARAVANCOURT
VARIABLE HOUNDSTEETH
VARIABLE DOCKSEVENTS
;----------------------------------------------
;       *** Lower Eltinmar Across/Ferry
;----------------------------------------------
NUMBER 524
NAME Grassland, Small Rise
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This rise marks the southern end of the lowlands. To the south, down a rocky
trail, lay the shores of the Inner Sea. The breeze gently ruffles the grass and
sparse shrubs resting at the top of this rise and harbors the rank and bitter
smell of the sea. Far to the north one can faintly see the chimneys and
rooftops of Fayd.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2301
EXIT N 522
ITEM 0 82 ADJ1=264 VAL2=525
;-------------------
NUMBER 2301
NAME Inner Sea Road
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing on the old road that runs along the inner sea cliffs toward
the West. It is impossibly old, composed of a material made before the
Cataclysm that rocked the world. It is unblemished in most places, no matter
what traffic has passed over it through the centuries.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 2302
EXIT E 524
;-------------------
NUMBER 2302
NAME Inner Sea Road
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing on the old road that runs along the inner sea cliffs toward
the West. It is impossibly old, composed of a material made before the
Cataclysm that rocked the world. It is unblemished in most places, no matter
what traffic has passed over it through the centuries. To the west you see the
wide mouth of the Eltinmar River as it pours into the Inner Sea. Across the
river you can see numerous buildings. To the north, in the rolling hills south
of the Kvantar Woods, are some small farming communities.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2301
EXIT SW 2303
;----------trail to Highridge-------
;ITEM 0 609 ADJ1=415 VAL2=3330
;---------------------------------
NUMBER 2303
NAME Lower Eltinmar, Eastern Dock
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A short wagon track leads away from the dock that you're on to the east and
the trail between Fayd and the beaches of the Inner Sea. The Eltinmar is wide
and slow here, flowing murkily toward the sea just out of sight to the south.
Across the wide river you can see a small town and some docks overlooked by a
stone tower on top of a steep hill. On this side are rows of burned and sacked
warehouses that once stored materials for shipment to and from Fayd. The
warehouses nearest the docks all bear the signs and crests of the various
guilds, nobles, and merchant houses that rented them. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 2302
;------------warehouse----------
ITEM 0 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
A huge warehouse sets here burned and looted by the order of the Way. The sign
over the door reads, "Royal Warehouse No. 6".  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------warehouse----------
ITEM 1 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
A huge warehouse sets here burned and looted by the order of the Way. The sign
over the door reads, "Property of the Arcana".  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------warehouse----------
ITEM 2 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
A steel and concrete warehouse sets here burned and looted by the order of the
Way. The sign over the door reads, "Technologists".  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-----------warehouse------------
ITEM 3 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
A huge warehouse sets here burned and looted by the order of the Way. The sign
over the door reads, "Warehouse 23 KEEP OUT".  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-------------------------------
IFITEM 6
        IFPREVERB GO 6
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You make your way down the short gangplank onto the wide ferry.
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way down the short gangplank onto the awaiting ferry.
                MOVE 2304
                AFFECT 2304
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way down the short gangplank from the dock toward you.
                AFFECT 2303
        ENDIF
ENDIF
;--------------------------
NUMBER 2304
NAME Commercial Ferry
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are on the commercial ferry that carries goods across the river for Fayd
and other towns on the Eastern shore of the Eltinmar river. It is wide of beam
and rather square shaped. Paddlewheels on each side of the craft push it
through the water at a good rate of speed for something so large. The river is
crowded here with various types of boats making their way with holds full of
sundry goods.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFITEM 6
        EQUAL COMMDOCK ITEMVAL2
        IFPREVERB GO 6
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the short gangplank onto the dock.
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank onto the dock.
                MOVE COMMDOCK
                AFFECT COMMDOCK
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank from the ferry toward you.
                AFFECT 2304
        ENDIF
ENDIF
;---------------------------
NUMBER 2305
NAME Lower Eltinmar, Western Dock
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
From your vantage on the short ferry dock, you can see the expanse of the
lower Eltinmar. The river is broad and slow here where its murky depths flow
into the Inner Sea. This side of the river is known by the highly original name
of Across. West of the dock you see the central plaza of the busy trading town.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2306
IFITEM 6
        IFPREVERB GO 6
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You make your way down the short gangplank onto the wide ferry.
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way down the short gangplank onto the awaiting ferry.
                MOVE 2304
                AFFECT 2304
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way down the short gangplank from the dock toward you.
                AFFECT 2320
        ENDIF
ENDIF
;-------------------------
NUMBER 2306
NAME Across Plaza
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is the center of the bustling trade center known as Across. To the east is
the broad Eltinmar river. Along the north of the plaza openings lead into shops
and stalls that sell a wide variety of things. The south side of the Plaza is
bordered by a large warehouse. To the west is a large building constructed of,
mud bricks while a steep road leads northwest up the side of a hill where a
tall stone tower broods over the town. In the center of the square sits a large
fountain for public water use.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2305
EXIT NW 2307
EXIT W 2308
;------------warehouse----------
ITEM 0 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
A huge warehouse sets here to store things awaiting either shipment to Fayd or
for the next caravan to depart across the western wastes.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
