NUMBER 2308
NAME Caravanserai
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here is the western edge of Across. Beyond this point to the west is the
endless wastelands. A large building surrounded by a wall sets here from which
daring and foolish people attempt to cross the trackless deserts for riches.
Constructed of mud bricks, the wall surrounding the Caravanserai is three to
five feet thick and over fifteen feet high. A large oak gate faces back toward
the plaza. It is usually kept open to allow access. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2306
;EXIT S 2331
ITEM 0 68 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=216 VAL2=2309 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;----------------------------
NUMBER 2309
NAME Caravanserai, Courtyard
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This court looks none too clean and stinks of animal dung, but at least its
paved. In the center stands a ten foot wide well. Next to the well is a
fountain basin of smooth granite which serves as a watering trough for the
mounts. The courtyard is open to the sky. On the south end of the courtyard is
the single storied building that houses the inn, stables and worker's quarters.
The stables are reserved for the mounts of caravan leaders or privileged
individuals. Common horses are boarded elsewhere. Other outbuildings in this
group house the inn's operator, his staff, and the drovers, porters, and guides
that work on a regular basis with the caravans.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2306
;------------gate out------
ITEM 0 68 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=216 VAL2=2308 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;------------inn----------
ITEM 1 465
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The inn is a mud brick building about twelve feet tall filling most of the
southern end of the Caravanserai Courtyard. A fenced enclosure is next to it.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------inn's door------
ITEM 2 65 ADJ2=355 VAL2=2322 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;--------basin--------------
ITEM 3 554 ADJ1=178
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The basin is large and the water is fresh.
*DESCRIPTION_END
PUT 3 198 VAL2=100 VAL3=0
;--------fence--------------
ITEM 4 1130 VAL2=2323
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The fence surrounds the stableyard and contains numerous animals.
*DESCRIPTION_END
