NUMBER 2310
NAME Riverview Tower
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here stands a square tower with rough stone walls, fifty-foot square and sixty-feet tall. A large iron bound oak gate leads inside the tower. The tower looks
formidable and the guardsmen on the roof seem alert.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 2307
;----------gate----------------
ITEM 0 68 ADJ1=169 ADJ2=1414 ADJ3=216 VAL1=99 VAL2=2311 VAL3=2311 CLOSED LOCKED
IFENTRY
  IFVAR DAY = 1
    ECHO PLAYER As you approach the tower you notice that the Royal Faydian Banner flies proudly from the ramparts of the tower.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER As you approach the tower you notice torches moving on the roof of the tower as the guards keep watch. 
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You seem to recall that King Frederick I built dozens of these towers to guard the frontier.
ENDIF
