NUMBER 2311
NAME Riverview Tower, Main Hall 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The garrison's eighteen guardsmen dwell in this great, open hall. The hall
fills this entire level of the tower. The walls are rough gray stone and the
floor and ceiling are rough hewn timbers. Cots and chests line the east and
west walls, and a fireplace sits in the southwest corner of the room. It is
used for cooking and heat. In the floor is a trapdoor and in the back is a
stairs leading to the floor above. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------------gate-------
