NUMBER 2316
NAME Riverview Tower, Armory 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The guards are allowed to keep short swords, knives and leather helmets with
their personal belongings in the Main Hall. Heavier weapons, missile weapons and
armor are stored here under the watchful eye of the garrison sergeant. The
armory holds enough bows, arrows, crossbows and bolts to hold off a small army
for several days, long enough for a messenger to reach Fayd and return with
reinforcements. As well it holds two dozen chainmail shirts and a like number
of small shields, spears and axes. Access is through the sergeant's quarters
and a stairs leads to the roof. A brass lamp illuminates the room.   
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------------opening-------
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=2314
;------------ stairs up  ---------------
ITEM 0 81 ADJ1=492 VAL2=2317
;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32
;----------------------------------------
NUMBER 2317
NAME Riverview Tower, Roof 
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The tower's roof is flat on top with a crenellated wall around the edges. From
here, watcher's can see to a distance of many miles in all directions,
including north to the Caldis Forests, east across the Eltinmar River, south
far out to sea, and west far into the endless western wastes. In times of need,
defenders can fire missile weapons and hurl stones from this roof to repel
attackers below. Torches mounted along the wall illuminate the area. A large
cauldron sits here. Stairs leads back down to the armory.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------ stairs down ---------------
ITEM 1 1226 ADJ1=493 VAL2=2316
;--------------cauldron-----------
ITEM 2 1169
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You look down to the front of the Tower.
  SHOWROOM 2310
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 2
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The cauldron is empty.
  ENDIF  
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You give the cauldron a mighty push, boiling oil falls down to the ground.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gives the cauldron a mighty push, sending boiling oil to the ground below.
    AFFECT 2310
    DAMAGEALL BURN 500 You are suddenly covered in boiling oil! 
    AFFECT 2317
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
    ECHO ALL Some guards begin to refill the cauldron.
    PLREVENT 6
    CONTPLREVENT
    EQUAL FLAG1 0
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;------------torches---------------
ITEM 2 373 
