NUMBER 2346
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Armory 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The guards are allowed to keep short swords, knives and leather helmets with
their personal belongings in the Main Hall. Heavier weapons, missile weapons and
armor are stored here under the watchful eye of the garrison sergeant. The
armory holds enough bows, arrows, crossbows and bolts to hold off a small army
for several days, long enough for a messenger to reach Fayd and return with
reinforcements. As well it holds two dozen chainmail shirts and a like number
of small shields, spears and axes. Access is through the sergeant's quarters
and a stairs leads to the roof. A brass lamp illuminates the room.   
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------------opening-------
