;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32
;----------------------------------------
NUMBER 2347
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Roof 
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The tower's roof is flat on top with a crenellated wall around the edges. From
here, watcher's can see to a distance of many miles in all directions. To the
west the Houndsteeth Mountains rise above you, while to the east the endless
wastelands seem to go on forever, separating you from the relative safety of
Fayd. In times of need, defenders can fire missile weapons and hurl stones from
this roof to repel attackers below. Torches mounted along the wall illuminate the
area. Stairs lead back down to the armory. A cauldron sits here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------ stairs down ---------------
ITEM 1 1226 ADJ1=493 VAL2=2346
;--------------cauldron-----------
ITEM 2 1169
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You look down to the front of the Tower.
  SHOWROOM 2340
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 2
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The cauldron is empty.
  ENDIF  
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You give the cauldron a mighty push, boiling oil falls down to the ground.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gives the cauldron a mighty push, sending boiling oil to the ground below.
    AFFECT 2340
    DAMAGEALL BURN 500 You are suddenly covered in boiling oil! 
    AFFECT 2347
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
    ECHO ALL Some guards begin to refill the cauldron.
    PLREVENT 6
    CONTPLREVENT
    EQUAL FLAG1 0
  ENDIF
ENDIF
